      • stack

        public static Stack stack(android.content.Context context,
                          java.lang.String stackApiKey,
                          java.lang.String accessToken,
                          java.lang.String environment)
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        Authenticates the stack api key of your stack. This must be called before your stack uses Built.io Contentstack sdk.
        You can find your stack api key from web.
        Parameters:
        context - application context.
        stackApiKey - application api Key of your application on Built.io Contentstack.
        accessToken - access token
        environment - environment name
        Returns:
        Stack instance.

        Example :
         //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Stack API key
 //'blt6d0240b5sample254090d' is dummy access token.
 Stack stack = Contentstack.stack(context, "blt5d4sample2633b", "blt6d0240b5sample254090d", "stag");
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • stack

        public static Stack stack(android.content.Context context,
                          java.lang.String stackApiKey,
                          java.lang.String accessToken,
                          java.lang.String environment,
                          Config config)
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        Authenticates the stack api key of your stack. This must be called before your stack uses Built.io Contentstack sdk.
        You can find your stack api key from web.
        Parameters:
        context - application context.
        stackApiKey - application api Key of your application on Built.io Contentstack.
        accessToken - access token
        config - Config instance to set environment and other configuration details.
        Returns:
        Stack instance.

        Example :
         //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Stack API key
 //'blt6d0240b5sample254090d' is dummy access token.
 Config config = new Config();
 config.setEnvironment("stag");

 Stack stack = Contentstack.stack(context, "blt5d4sample2633b", "blt6d0240b5sample254090d", config);
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
